  "prompt": "Does a user always need to keep the data \u2018ON\u2019 for outgoing/incoming calls on Jio network?",
  "response": "For using Jio network services such as outgoing and incoming calls, the data does not necessarily need to be kept 'ON' at all times. Here's how it works:\n\n1. **VoLTE Calls**: Jio primarily uses Voice over LTE (VoLTE) for calls, which means voice calls are transmitted over the internet. When you make or receive a call, your phone automatically uses the data connection for the call. However, you don't need to manually keep the data 'ON' because the phone manages this switch automatically.\n\n2. **Data Usage**: Even if your mobile data is turned 'OFF', you can still make and receive calls because the phone will turn on the data just for the duration of the call and then turn it off again once the call is over.\n\n3. **Settings**: Some phones might have specific settings related to VoLTE or data usage during calls. Make sure these settings are configured correctly to allow automatic data usage for calls.\n\nIn summary, you don't need to manually keep the data 'ON' for Jio calls. The phone handles this automatically, ensuring you can make and receive calls without any manual intervention regarding data settings.",
